<!--
Two independent axes — keep them honest:
  Status         — the document:   draft -> active -> deprecated
  Implementation — the capability: planned -> partial -> implemented -> verified
Flip Status to "active" only once this spec reflects intended truth.
Advance Implementation as code lands; "verified" means a test proves it
(cite the test per acceptance criterion — see `doctrina coverage`).
An "active" spec left at "planned" is an inventory claim with nothing
behind it, and `doctrina validate` warns. To record a deliberate gap and
silence the warning, add a note after the value, e.g.
"**Implementation:** planned — backend deferred to Q3, see ADR 0007".

Realizes ties this capability to product intent (`doctrina trace`;
ADR 0006). Tag product.md success-criteria bullets with an anchor —
"- [SC1] ..." — and list the ones this spec delivers above. An "active"
spec with no Realizes: header warns under `doctrina validate`; if the
capability genuinely maps to no product anchor (internal tooling), keep
the header and write "n/a — <why>" to record that on purpose.
-->

